HSBC Cuts Its S&P 500 2011 Year-End Forecast to 1,130 From 1,430

-- B y   J o a n n a   O s s i n g e r
-- 
2011-10-10T14:24:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/hsbc-cuts-its-s-p-500-2011-year-end-forecast-to-1-130-from-1-430.html
The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index will
end the year at 1,130, HSBC Holdings Plc said, reducing its
estimate from a prior 1,430.  Garry Evans , HSBC’s global head of equity strategy who
makes the predictions, doesn’t have a forecast for earnings per
share by companies in the gauge.  The  S&P 500  rose 2.8 percent to 1,187.71 at 10:24 a.m. New
York time today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joanna Ossinger at 
 jossinger@bloomberg.net  